name: AstraZeneca Covid vaccine
summary: AstraZeneca has acknowledged in court documents that its COVID-19 vaccine carries the potential to cause a rare side effect known as thrombosis with thrombocytopenia syndrome (TTS). This admission emerged during a legal confrontation with individuals who claimed to have experienced TTS following vaccination. TTS is characterized by unusual blood clotting and low platelet levels, potentially leading to serious complications. However, AstraZeneca emphasizes the rarity of this side effect, highlighting that only a small number of cases have been reported globally. The admission serves as a reminder of the ongoing surveillance and monitoring of vaccine safety, as evidenced by the vigilance and transparency of AstraZeneca and regulatory bodies.

name: Rory Sloane
summary: Adelaide Crows captain Rory Sloane has announced his retirement from the AFL due to a rare eye condition that has detached his retina. Sloane made the "heartbreaking" decision after extensive medical advice revealed the risks of further damage to his eye were too great. The 33-year-old's retirement ends a remarkable career that spanned 255 AFL games, including 153 as captain. His decision has sent shockwaves through the AFL community, with the Adelaide Crows, AFL players, and fans expressing their sadness and support.
